"Bauer D., Marx R., Nußbicker-Lux J., Ochs F., Heidemann W., Müller-Steinhagen H.","German central solar heating plants with seasonal heat storage",2010,"Solar Energy","84","4",,"612","623",,,10.1016/j.solener.2009.05.013,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-77649234991&partnerID=40&md5=964ba8c4969c7d86547e730be4629b08","Institute of Thermodynamics and Thermal Engineering (ITW), University of Stuttgart, Pfaffenwaldring 6, D-70550 Stuttgart, Germany; Institute of Technical Thermodynamics (ITT), German Aerospace Centre (DLR), Stuttgart, Germany","Bauer, D., Institute of Thermodynamics and Thermal Engineering (ITW), University of Stuttgart, Pfaffenwaldring 6, D-70550 Stuttgart, Germany; Marx, R., Institute of Thermodynamics and Thermal Engineering (ITW), University of Stuttgart, Pfaffenwaldring 6, D-70550 Stuttgart, Germany; Nußbicker-Lux, J., Institute of Thermodynamics and Thermal Engineering (ITW), University of Stuttgart, Pfaffenwaldring 6, D-70550 Stuttgart, Germany; Ochs, F., Institute of Thermodynamics and Thermal Engineering (ITW), University of Stuttgart, Pfaffenwaldring 6, D-70550 Stuttgart, Germany; Heidemann, W., Institute of Thermodynamics and Thermal Engineering (ITW), University of Stuttgart, Pfaffenwaldring 6, D-70550 Stuttgart, Germany; Müller-Steinhagen, H., Institute of Thermodynamics and Thermal Engineering (ITW), University of Stuttgart, Pfaffenwaldring 6, D-70550 Stuttgart, Germany, Institute of Technical Thermodynamics (ITT), German Aerospace Centre (DLR), Stuttgart, Germany","Central solar heating plants contribute to the reduction of CO2-emissions and global warming. The combination of central solar heating plants with seasonal heat storage enables high solar fractions of 50% and more. Several pilot central solar heating plants with seasonal heat storage (CSHPSS) built in Germany since 1996 have proven the appropriate operation of these systems and confirmed the high solar fractions. Four different types of seasonal thermal energy stores have been developed, tested and monitored under realistic operation conditions: Hot-water thermal energy store (e.g. in Friedrichshafen), gravel-water thermal energy store (e.g. in Steinfurt-Borghorst), borehole thermal energy store (in Neckarsulm) and aquifer thermal energy store (in Rostock). In this paper, measured heat balances of several German CSHPSS are presented. The different types of thermal energy stores and the affiliated central solar heating plants and district heating systems are described. Their operational characteristics are compared using measured data gained from an extensive monitoring program. Thus long-term operational experiences such as the influence of net return temperatures are shown. © 2009 Elsevier Ltd. All rights reserved.","Central solar heating plant; Seasonal heat storage; Solar assisted district heating; UTES","Central solar heating plant; District heating system; Germany; Heat balance; Measured data; Monitoring programs; Net return; Operation conditions; Operational characteristics; Operational experience; Solar assisted district heating; Solar fraction; Solar heating plant; Aquifers; District heating; Global warming; Heat storage; Heating equipment; Retail stores; Solar energy; Solar heating; Space heating; Thermal energy; Heating; carbon dioxide; emission control; global warming; heat balance; heating; photovoltaic system; solar power",,,,,,"Bauer, D., Heidemann, W., Marx, R., Nußbicker-Lux, J., Ochs, F., Panthalookaran, V., Raab, S., 2008. Solar unterstützte Nahwärme und Langzeit-Wärmespeicher (Juni 2005 bis Juli 2008). Forschungsbericht zum BMU-Vorhaben 0329607J, StuttgartBenner, M., Bodmann, M., Mangold, D., Nußbicker, J., Raab, S., Schmidt, T., Seiwald, H., Solar unterstützte Nahwärmeversorgung mit und ohne Langzeit-Wärmespeicher (November 1998 bis Januar 2003) (2003) Forschungsbericht zum BMWi-Vorhaben, , 0329606 S, ISBN 3-9805274-2-5, Stuttgart; Bodmann, M., Mangold, D., Nußbicker, J., Raab, S., Schenke, A., Schmidt, T., 2005. Solar unterstützte Nahwärme und Langzeit-Wärmespeicher (Februar 2003 bis Mai 2005). Forschungsbericht zum BMWA/BMU-Vorhaben 0329607F, StuttgartFisch, M.N., Guigas, M., Dalenbäck, J.O., A review of large-scale solar heating systems in Europe (1998) Solar Energy, 63 (6), pp. 355-366; Hahne, E., The ITW solar heating system: an oldtimer fully in action (2000) Solar Energy, 69 (6), pp. 469-493; Hahne, E., Benner, M., Ebel, M., Mahler, B., Mangold, D., Schmidt, T., Schulz, M., Seiwald, H., (1998) Solare Nahwärme - Ein Leitfaden für die Praxis, BINE-Informationspaket, , TÜV-Verlag, Köln; Herb, A., (2007) Auslegung und Optimierung der hydraulischen und regelungstechnischen Einbindung eines Erdbeckenspeichers für das Solarkonzept Schulzentrum Eggenstein, Diplomarbeit, Hochschule für angewandte Wissenschaft Hamburg, , Fakultät Life Sciences, Hamburg; Lichtenfels, A., Reineck, K.H., The design and construction of the concrete hot water tank in Friedrichshafen for the seasonal storage of solar energy (2000) Proc. 8th Int. Conference on Thermal Energy Storage, TERRASTOCK, 1, pp. 257-262. , Stuttgart, pp; Mangold, D., 2007. 10 Jahre saisonale Wärmespeicherung von Solarwärme: Entwicklungsstand und Perspektiven, 17. Symposium Thermische Solarenergie, 09.-11. Mai 2007, Kloster Banz, Bad StaffelsteinMeliß, M., Säte, F., The solar heating system with seasonal storage at the solar campus Jülich (2000) Solar Energy, 69 (6), pp. 525-533; Nußbicker, J., Mangold, D., Heidemann, W., Müller-Steinhagen, H., Solar assisted district heating system with duct thermal energy store in Neckarsulm-Amorbach (Germany) (2003) Proc. ISES Solar World Congress 2003, Göteborg (Schweden), ISBN: 91-631-4740-8 (CD); Nußbicker, J., Mangold, D., Heidemann, W., Müller-Steinhagen, H., Solar assisted district heating system with seasonal duct thermal energy store in Neckarsulm-Amorbach (Germany) (2004) Proc. EuroSun2004, 14. Internationales Sonnenforum, 1, pp. 509-517. , Freiburg i. Br, ISBN: 3-98096